error: Module evaluation is still pending but there are no pending ops or dynamic imports. This situation is often caused by unresolved promises.
```

This can also happen with `deno test`:

```js
Deno.test("resolve on beforeunload", async () => {
  await new Promise(resolve => {
    window.onbeforeunload = resolve;
  });
});
```

```
running 1 test from ./a.test.js
resolve on beforeunload ...
FAILED | 0 passed | 0 failed (20ms)

error: Promise resolution is still pending but the event loop has already resolved.
```

These errors show up because Deno's event loop assumes that a promise that's holding up a module's top-level await (or in the case of `deno test`, a call to `JsRuntime::poll_value`) will resolve within the event loop, and so if there are no ref'd async ops that can cause some more code to run, the promise won't ever resolve. But the `beforeunload` event is fired from the CLI crate and the event loop doesn't know about it.

This is not specific to the `beforeunload` event, since it can also happen with promises that resolve on the `unload` event. The difference is that nothing other than microtasks will run after the `unload` event, whereas the event loop might keep running after `beforeunload`.

