~~Certain emscripten files~~ **Any file that includes `eval()`** causes the bundler to generate files with syntax errors, due to duplicate identifiers. There is no wasm loaded: simply importing the module wrapper is enough to cause it. The same code runs fine via `deno run`, but when bundled it does not dedupe identifiers. The following is a minimal repro:

```typescript
// index.ts
import { hello as hello1 } from "./hello.ts";
import { hello as hello2 } from "./hello2.ts";
function doEval() {
  eval("console.log('hello');");
}
console.log(hello1, hello2, doEval);
```

